CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 3, 1955, pg. 17 reads: "Plan Bi-Centennial - Members of the executive committee for Pittsburgh's Bi-Centennial celebration in 1958, held their initial meeting in Board Room of the Community Chest Building, last week, and began planning for the historic event. Left to right, seated, A. W. Connover, C. Lawrence Woods and James F. Hillman.  Standing, left to right, John P. Robin, Councilman Paul F. Jones and John A. Feigal. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of executive committee for Pittsburgh's bicentennial celebration in 1958, from left, seated: A. W. Connover, C. Lawrence Woods, and James F. Hillman; standing: John P. Robin, Paul F. Jones, and John A. Feigal, in board room in Community Chest Building
